---
/**
 * Privacy Policy Page
 *
 * Covers:
 * - Analytics (Vercel Web Analytics)
 * - Affiliate tracking
 * - Cookies and local storage
 * - Data collection practices
 *
 * @module pages/privacy
 */

import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  meta={{
    title: "Privacy Policy | StackHunt",
    description: "Learn how StackHunt collects, uses, and protects your data. Our privacy practices for analytics, cookies, and affiliate tracking."
  }}
>
  <main class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert max-w-none prose-headings:text-zinc-100 prose-p:text-zinc-400 prose-a:text-indigo-400 hover:prose-a:text-indigo-300 prose-strong:text-zinc-200 prose-li:text-zinc-400">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

      <p class="lead text-xl text-zinc-400">
        Last updated: January 2026
      </p>

      <p>
        StackHunt ("we," "us," or "our") respects your privacy and is committed to
        protecting your personal data. This privacy policy explains how we collect,
        use, and safeguard information when you visit stackhunt.com.
      </p>

      <h2>Information We Collect</h2>

      <h3>Analytics Data</h3>
      <p>
        We use <strong>Vercel Web Analytics</strong> to understand how visitors use our site.
        This privacy-focused analytics service collects:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Page views and navigation patterns</li>
        <li>Referral sources (how you found us)</li>
        <li>Device type and browser information</li>
        <li>Geographic region (country/region level only)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Vercel Web Analytics is designed to be privacy-friendly and does not use cookies
        for tracking. It does not collect personally identifiable information (PII) and
        is compliant with GDPR, CCPA, and other privacy regulations.
      </p>

      <h3>Voting and Interaction Data</h3>
      <p>
        When you upvote or downvote tools on StackHunt, we collect:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>A hashed browser fingerprint (to prevent duplicate votes)</li>
        <li>A hashed IP address (for rate limiting and fraud prevention)</li>
        <li>Your vote direction (up or down)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We hash these identifiers using one-way encryption, meaning we cannot reverse
        them to identify you personally. This data is used solely to ensure fair voting
        and prevent abuse.
      </p>

      <h3>Local Storage</h3>
      <p>
        We use your browser's local storage to save:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your "My Stack" selections (tools you've saved for comparison)</li>
        <li>Your voting history (to show you how you voted)</li>
        <li>UI preferences</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This data never leaves your device and is not transmitted to our servers.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies</h2>

      <h3>Essential Cookies</h3>
      <p>
        We use minimal essential cookies required for the site to function:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Session cookies</strong> — Used for admin authentication only. Regular visitors do not receive session cookies.</li>
        <li><strong>Security tokens</strong> — Cloudflare Turnstile may set cookies to verify you're not a bot when voting.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Third-Party Cookies</h3>
      <p>
        Some of our affiliate partners may set cookies when you click on affiliate links.
        These cookies help track referrals so we can earn a commission if you make a purchase.
        These are set by the merchant's website, not by StackHunt.
      </p>

      <h2>Affiliate Link Tracking</h2>

      <p>
        StackHunt participates in affiliate programs with various software companies and
        affiliate networks (such as Impact and PartnerStack). When you click an affiliate
        link on our site:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>We record that a click occurred (to measure our content's effectiveness)</li>
        <li>You are redirected to the merchant's website</li>
        <li>The merchant may set their own tracking cookies</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not share your personal information with affiliate partners. The click data
        we collect is aggregated and anonymized.
      </p>
      <p>
        For more information about our affiliate relationships, see our{' '}
        <a href="/disclosure" class="text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300">Affiliate Disclosure</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>

      <p>We use collected information to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Improve our content and user experience</li>
        <li>Prevent abuse and ensure fair voting</li>
        <li>Measure the effectiveness of our content</li>
        <li>Understand aggregate usage patterns</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do <strong>not</strong> sell, rent, or share your personal information with
        third parties for their marketing purposes.
      </p>

      <h2>Data Retention</h2>

      <p>
        Analytics data is retained for up to 12 months in aggregated form. Vote records
        are retained indefinitely to maintain voting integrity, but contain only hashed
        identifiers that cannot be linked back to you.
      </p>

      <h2>Your Rights</h2>

      <p>Depending on your location, you may have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Access the personal data we hold about you</li>
        <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
        <li>Opt out of certain data collection</li>
        <li>Lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Since we collect minimal personal data and use privacy-focused analytics, there
        is typically little to no personal data to access or delete. If you have concerns,
        please contact us.
      </p>

      <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>

      <p>
        StackHunt is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect
        personal information from children under 13. If you believe we have inadvertently
        collected such information, please contact us so we can delete it.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>

      <p>
        We may update this privacy policy from time to time. We will notify you of any
        changes by posting the new policy on this page and updating the "Last updated"
        date at the top.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact Us</h2>

      <p>
        If you have questions about this privacy policy or our data practices, please
        contact us at:{' '}
        <a href="mailto:privacy@stackhunt.com" class="text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300">
          privacy@stackhunt.com
        </a>
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8" />

      <p class="text-sm text-zinc-500">
        This policy is effective as of January 2026.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
